I would notice 2 - but the real kicker is that some seconds I could see from my log that I had gotten 3 or 4 attacks.<br><br>The <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> only</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> explanation for this is that I had two attack rounds in that second, ie. delay was less than 10.<br><br>Just apply a little logic as well, if there was a min. delay on 10 - no monk would ever benefit from upgrading from Epic haste + FBSS, they would literally be at 10delay with that equipment - that's rediculous, even a monk should be able to figure that out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  - in fact, it was a monk that told me this curiousum.<br><br>In conclusion:<br><br>No, there is not a minimum delay of 10 - there might be a minimum delay, but if there is, then it is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> definitely</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> lower than 10. I'm almost 100% sure that people just browse their logs, they see that no attacks are made inbetween seconds (well, duh - EQ doesn't record 10ths of seconds) and conclude that the lowest delay possible must be 10, which is a load of crack smoking logic. <p><big><center><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=19405 target=blank>Marshall Sscaley Iceblade</a><br><i><a href=http://companions.windsofstorm.net>The Companions</a></i> <br>Warlizard on Tribunal</big><br><small>"Tails are not for biting or pulling!"</small></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dobbofutreet>Dobbo Futreet</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 227<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/26/02 9:04:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fth